A major pet food recall was announced after reports of vomiting, kidney failure, and deaths in dogs and cats across North America.
Menu Foods, a prominent manufacturer, recalled millions of containers of wet pet food sold under various brand names.
Concerned pet owners scrambled for information as retailers removed the suspect items from shelves.
The company identified a new ingredient as a potential cause of contamination but has not pinpointed the exact issue.
Veterinarians urged pet owners to watch for symptoms of kidney failure, including lethargy and loss of appetite.
The recall affected popular brands like Iams, Nutro, and Eukanuba.
